Introduction

Nishimura Riki, known under his stage name Ni-ki, is a Japanese dancer, rapper, singer-songwriter, and composer under Belift Lab. He is best known as the maknae and main dancer of the boy group ENHYPEN.

On June 1, 2020, Ni-ki was introduced as a contestant in the CJ ENM and Big Hit Entertainment's reality survival show I-LAND. On September 18, 2020, he ranked 4th place by global votes and became a member of ENHYPEN.

Ni-ki made his debut as a member of ENHYPEN on November 30, 2020, with their first mini album "Border : Day One".
